<TEXT>
louisiana insurance commissioner doug 
green and his wife and brother entered innocent pleas thursday to 
charges they took bribes to keep a floundering insurance company 
from going under 
the trio was indicted by a grand jury in east baton rouge parish 
on june 28 
doug green is accused of accepting bribes from champion 
insurance co officials while he was a candidate for the 
commissioners post in 1987 with an eye toward helping the company 
stay alive once he took office 
the second count in the state indictment charged that while 
green was in he and his wife linn and brother donald accepted or 
offered to accept bribes to influence greens conduct 
judge l j hymel set bond at 25000 for each of the three and 
they were booked and released 
hymel said he would set a trial date in september green also 
faces federal charges stemming from the champion scandal 
champion failed on june 5 1989 more than a year after green 
took office the company left unpaid claims in louisiana estimated 
at between 150 million and 180 million a debt that will be 
covered by state taxpayers under louisianas insurance system 
champion was the thirdlargest automobile insurer in the state 
the company also left an estimated 45 million in claims in 
alabama and an undetermined amount in tennessee 
champion owner john eicher jr his son naaman and other members 
of their family already have pleaded guilty to various federal 
charges stemming from the champion failure 
</TEXT>
