<TEXT>
here is a brief chronology of the pete rose case 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
jan 25 a piksix at cincinnatiarea racetrack has two winning 
tickets worth 13283460 each rumors surface that rose was one of 
ticket owners 
march 20 baseball commissioners office releases statement 
that it is investigating serious allegations against rose and 
that washington lawyer john m dowd is heading inquiry 
march 21 sports illustrated story contains allegations tying 
rose to baseball betting 
march 25 turfway park statement says rose was an owner of 
winning piksix tickets 
march 26 the cleveland plain dealer reports rose was target of 
undercover gambling investigations conducted by cincinnati police 
department in 1978 and 1983 
april 5 plain dealer reports a man listed in court documents 
by code name g1 and identified by sources as rose bet between 
8000 to 16000 daily on baseball games during the 1987 season 
april 21 robert c brichler an assistant us attorney says 
rose is being investigated by grand jury on tax matters 
may 9 baseball commissioner a bartlett giamatti receives 
225page report on rose from dowd 
june 21 the associated press reports baseballs handwriting 
expert determined roses writing is on betting slips 
aug 24 giamatti announces pete rose is banned for life from 
baseball for gambling he may apply for reinstatement after one 
year 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
april 20 in us district court in cincinnati rose pleads 
guilty to two counts of filing false incomes taxes by failing to 
report income 
july 19 us district judge s arthur spiegel sentences rose 
to five months in prison and three months in a halfway house fines 
him 50000 and orders him to perform 1000 hours of community 
service with innercity youths 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

