<TEXT>
marlon brandos daughter was served with a 
subpoena in tahiti to testify against her halfbrother who is 
charged with killing her boyfriend authorities said thursday 
it was not immediately clear whether cheyenne brando will return 
to los angeles in time for mondays hearing for 32yearold 
christian brando an american diplomat served the notice to her in 
papeete on wednesday 
miss brando 20 left for french polynesia after refusing to 
testify against her halfbrother who is accused of the may 16 
shooting death of dag drollet at her fathers estate in the santa 
monica mountains 
the case is complicated by reports that authorities in tahiti 
filed a complaint allowing them to question miss brando in the 
killing and that she was forbidden to leave french polynesia for 
the time being 
further clouding the matter is that miss brando is believed to 
hold both american and french passports 
sandi gibbons a spokeswoman for the los angeles county district 
attorneys office said that extradition procedures would be 
unnecessary in any case because miss brando is wanted by los 
angeles authorities as a witness not as a suspect 
drollet the father of miss brandos unborn child was gunned 
down at marlon brandos estate the actor was home at the time of 
the slaying but he was elsewhere in the house and did not see it 
christian brando reportedly told police that drollet died during 
a struggle over a gun 
miss brando a native of the south pacific islands is the 
daughter of brando and his current wife tarita teriipia miss 
teriipia is the tahitian actress who played his love interest in 
the 1962 remake of mutiny on the bounty 
miss brando returned to french polynesia eight months pregnant 
with the child of her slain boyfriend she gave birth and is now in 
a tahitian hospital undergoing treatment for nervous exhaustion 
marlon brando maintains a home in tahiti 
