<TEXT>
like douglas wilder in 1989 and andrew 
young this year abdul alim muhammad is waging an uphill battle for 
political office like them he is black but there is a difference 
there is nothing colorblind about muhammads campaign for 
congress he is the candidate of the nation of islam the 
fundamentalist muslim organization long regarded as a bastion of 
black separatism 
this year for the first time the group headed by louis 
farrakhan is exploring the political mainstream running three 
candidates with its official endorsement 
it is highly likely this is not the last time we are going to 
be involved in electoral politics muhammad said in an interview 
at his storefront campaign headquarters in marylands prince 
georges county just outside washington 
the other two candidates are george cure a legal adviser to the 
nation of islam who is running for the district of columbias 
nonvoting delegate seat in congress and shawn brakeen a 
schoolteacher candidate for the districts school board 
the muslim movement has espoused racial separation since it 
began nearly 60 years ago but muhammad said we have never been 
isolated we believe that where we are dominant in numbers we 
should have a position of leadership that is representative of our 
numbers 
my objective in congress will be to inspire and organize and 
secure resources so that prince georges county will be a 
shining light an example of what highly motivated blacks can do to 
pull themselves up by their own bootstraps so to speak said 
muhammad 
farrakhan has been criticized for making comments offensive to 
jews and other ethnic groups but he said recently that the muslim 
candidates would represent all people regardless of their race 
creed or color 
the emergence of nation of islam candidates comes amid growing 
black prominence in american politics 
wilder the former virginia lieutenant governor became the 
nations first elected black governor last year after successfully 
courting both black and white voters 
young a civil rights leader and former mayor of atlanta 
finished second in georgias democratic gubernatorial primary on 
tuesday and faces a runoff aug 7 against lt gov zell miller 
some black leaders have criticized young for running a colorblind 
campaign in an effort to woo white support in a state where about 
22 percent of the registered voters are black 
muhammad said it was understandable for wilder and young to 
reach out to white voters but he said such crossover 
politicians do not provide the same leadership for the black 
community as would a black leader 
andy young cant win with the black vote in atlanta he 
said he needs some of the rural white vote to win at least some 
of those voters he has to be what is called a crossover candidate 
blacks have to understand that it is possible for blacks to be 
leaders in that sense but they should not expect from this kind of 
crossover politician the kind of thing you would expect from a 
black leader 
doug wilder has become governor of all the people of virginia 
but he should not be mistaken for a black leader who is going to do 
very much to correct the wrongs in the black community he said 
muhammad 42 a surgeon who is farrakhans spokesman is running 
in the sept 11 primary against steny hoyer chairman of the house 
democratic caucus hoyer 50 has represented marylands 5th 
congressional district for four terms and is strongly favored for 
reelection 
the district which includes most of prince georges county is 
about evenly divided between black and white with the black 
population increasing 
as almost all candidates do muhammad said he expects to win 
hoyer however has a strong lead in fundraising having raised 
453000 for his campaign before he announced muhammad has been 
raising funds among blacks in the washington area as well as in 
philadelphia and other cities 
muhammad declined to say how much had been raised but said the 
campaign had been advised it need not file with the federal 
election commission an fec spokesman said a campaign must file 
with the commission if it has raised more than 5000 
although the nation of islam has not previously endorsed 
candidates muhammad said individual members have run from time to 
time on their own 
dr talibkarim muhammad for instance already has announced 
his candidacy for mayor of memphis tenn in an election to be 
held oct 3 1991 
