said but we needed this money we were taken completely by 
surprise on these cuts and raising a ruckus seemed the only way to 
get this money back 
appropriations committee members said they had agreed to the 
cuts because much of the money in the programs 1990 budget had not 
yet been spent 
natcher in an interview said only 29 percent of 11 billion 
in block grants to the states for drug treatment had been spent in 
the first 9 months of the current fiscal year 
i dont want to get in any disagreement with bill bennett 
