assistance for treatment 
the bill provides 76 billion for the department of labor in 
fiscal 1991 it authorizes 1357 billion for the department of 
health and human services 26 billion for the department of 
education and 1 billion for related agencies 
the total represents a 173 billion increase over 1990 spending 
and a 42 billion increase over the amount requested by bush in 
his proposed 1991 budget 
