<TEXT>
the korean peninsula was divided into 
communist north korea and capitalist south korea at the end of 
world war ii in 1945 following is a chronology on relations 
aug 15 1945 korea was liberated from 35 years of japanese 
colonial rule in the postwar politics korea was divided along the 
38th parallel with soviet union troops in the north and us troops 
in the south 
1948 north korea established a communist dictatorship headed by 
kim il sung south korea held elections and established a 
ussupported government headed by syngman rhee 
1950 north korea invaded south korea triggering a bitter 
threeyear civil war an estimated 24 million soldiers and 44 
million civilians were killed or wounded on both sides 
1953 the korean war ended with an armistice and a 25milewide 
demilitarized zone was established dividing the peninsula a peace 
treaty was never signed 
1968 a group of 31 north korean commandos tried unsuccessfully 
to assassinate thenpresident park chunghee the us 
reconnaissance ship pueblo was captured by north korea for 
allegedly sailing into its territorial waters the crew was 
released 11 months later 
1972 the koreas issued a joint statement renouncing hostilities 
and pledging peaceful unification of the peninsula but talks fail 
1974 the first of four tunnels allegedly dug by north korea for 
an invasion under the demilitarized zone was unearthed by south 
korea other tunnels were found in 1975 1978 and 1990 north korea 
denied digging them 
1976 north korean security guards killed two us soldiers with 
axes in a dispute over pruning a tree in the demilitarized zone 
1983 north korean commandos bombed a cemetery in rangoon 
burma killing 17 south korean officials including four cabinet 
ministers accompanying thenpresident chun doohwan 
1985 151 people including art performers and journalists from 
each side visited the korean capitals in an exchange and reunion of 
separated families 
1987 two north korean terrorists bombed a south korean airliner 
over the andaman sea near burma killing all 115 people aboard one 
terrorist was captured and sentenced to death in seoul she was 
pardoned and released in 1990 on grounds she had been duped and 
repented her actions 
1988 the summer olympic games were held in seoul with 160 
nations attending north korea boycotted the games 
1989 south korea jailed five people including a radical 
student and and an opposition lawmaker for defying a government 
ban on travel to north korea 
1990 north korea boycotted interkorea talks for six months 
demanding the annual ussouth korean military maneuvers be 
canceled and us troops be withdrawn 
january north korea demanded south korea tear down a 
berlintype border wall south korea says the alleged wall is a 
series of tank traps 
july 3 the two koreas agreed to hold their first prime 
ministers talks propably in september an accord arranging the 
date and an agenda was to be signed july 26 
july 6 north korea said it would open a small portion of its 
border inside the demilitarized zone aug 15 to welcome south 
koreans desiring unification it also said seoul must abolish 
anticommunist laws 
july 20 south korean president roh taewoo proposes to open the 
border for five days beginning aug 13 
</TEXT>
