<TEXT>
here are some key dates in the ethics 
investigation into rep barney frank dmass 
july 1985 after paying male prostitute stephen gobie for sex 
frank hires gobie using personal funds as a housekeeper and 
driver hoping to change his way of life 
may 1987 in response to a reporters question frank publicly 
acknowledges for the first time that he is gay 
august 1987 frank ends his relationship with gobie after 
learning that gobie was running a prostitution ring out of franks 
capitol hill apartment gobie later claims frank was aware of the 
prostitution all along and that claim becomes a major issue in the 
ethics case 
november 1988 frank wins election to a fifth term by a 7030 
margin 
aug 25 1989 the washington times reports that frank paid 
gobie for sex and hired him to do chores it is the first public 
word of franks relationship with gobie 
sept 10 1989 a boston sunday globe editorial calls on frank 
to resign for his own good and for the good of his constituents 
his causes and congress 
sept 11 1989 the house ethics committee votes to conduct an 
investigation into franks relationship with gobie frank says he 
wont resign and will decide his political plans after the 
committee completes its investigation he apologizes to his 
constituents for some serious mistakes in judgment several years 
ago what i did was wrong he says in a newsweek interview that 
gobie was not the first prostitute he hired 
oct 20 1989 the washington times reports that gobie claims 
he and frank had sex in the house gymnasium frank denies it 
oct 30 1989 the ethics committee holds the first of several 
closeddoor meetings on the frank case 
dec 5 1989 gobie testifies 
jan 23 1990 rep william dannemeyer rcalif says he plans 
to demand that the house cast a rollcall vote on a proposal to 
expel frank 
feb 6 1990 penthouse magazine publishes an interview of 
gobie who received 50000 from the magazine that breaks little 
new ground 
april 17 1990 frank announces plans to seek a sixth term 
april 2526 1990 the ethics committee holds two marathon 
sessions sources indicate that democrats want to issue frank a 
letter reproving his conduct republicans are said to be pushing 
for a tougher sanction 
may 10 1990 a former prostitute testifies before the 
committee after alleging publicly that frank knew the sexforhire 
ring was being operated from his apartment frank denies it 
producing an affidavit from his landlady that she believed frank 
was unaware of the prostitution 
july 19 1990 the ethics committee recommends that the house 
reprimand frank 
