council in october and the government said it hoped flogging would 
be abolished this year 
the punishment administered with a light cane was introduced 
in hong kong in the heyday of the british empire its use has 
declined in recent years hong kong courts ordered only two 
floggings last year compared with 476 in 1952 officials said 
under existing laws only men can be flogged the number of 
strokes range from 18 for offenders age 17 or older to six for 
offenders under 14 
a court can order floggings for offenses that include indecent 
assault robbery rape of a woman under 16 weapons possession and 
piracy 
flogging was abolished in britain about four decades ago and 
the hong kong government has been encouraged to end the practice 
because of international criticism 
</TEXT>
