unfair and a form of censorship 
ramos agreed that the rating system used by the motion picture 
association of america sevenmember ratings board is an effective 
form of censorship but he said the petition before his court was 
not the proper vehicle for relief 
the mpaa says its rating system is a guide for parents to make 
judgments about which movies they want their children to see it is 
not designed to rate the merits of a film the mpaa says 
the mpaa said almodovars movie whose spanish title is 
atame was rated x because of a prolonged and graphic 
sex scene photographed from numerous angles and accompanied by an 
explicit sound track 
ramos said nothing supports the mpaas claim that its ratings 
are designed to protect children no physicians child 
psychiatrists or child care professionals are on the board nor is 
guidance from such professionals sought the judge noted 
ramos said that the rating systems categories have been 
fashioned by the motion picture industry to create an illusion of 
concern for children imposing censorship yet all the while 
facilitating the marketing of exploitive and violent films with an 
industry seal of approval 
notably absent from the ratings system is any sensitivity to 
the offenses suffered by women minorities the disabled and those 
who may not share the values of the average american parent 
ramos said 
a film may be viewed by children that may contain hard 
violence and drug use but not explicit sex he said it may 
be that the mpaa ratings are skewed toward permitting film makers 
huge profits pandering to the appetite for films containing hard 
violence and drug use while neglecting the welfare of children 
