a problem with ground equipment 
delayed todays blastoff of an atlas rocket at least an hour 
putting off the rockets commercial launch debut on a flight to 
carry a satellite that will illuminate earths magnetic field 
nasa and general dynamics had planned to launch the unmanned 
rocket from cape canaveral air force station sometime between 333 
and 346 pm but workers could not start a compressor that 
furnishes gaseous nitrogen to the rocket to keep the satellite cool 
if the compressor can be started in time officials planned to 
