radiation effects satellite known as crres to an elliptical orbit 
217 miles by 22236 miles high 
the satellite is a joint program of the national aeronautics and 
space administration and the defense department 
nasa is overseeing the satellites release of 24 aluminum 
canisters at various altitudes during the next year one or two 
canisters will be ejected at a time releasing chemicals that will 
form large glowing clouds similar in appearance to the aurora 
borealis or the northern lights 
the clouds will spread along earths invisible magnetic field 
lines making them visible to the naked eye 
scientists will study the clouds interaction with charged 
particles in the ionosphere and magnetosphere 
the first canisters will be released in september over the south 
pacific the first releases visible over north america will be in 
early 1991 
two such releases already have been made over northern canada 
originating from a pegasus airlaunched rocket in april unmanned 
sounding rockets will drop similar canisters this summer and again 
in 1991 
air force instruments aboard the 2ton satellite will probe the 
van allen radiation belts encircling earth microelectronic 
components also will be exposed to space radiation to determine 
whether they could fail in future flights 
the satellite originally was to have been deployed in 1987 from 
the space shuttle but the 1986 challenger disaster pushed back the 
