an indianapolis radio station has been fined 
10000 for broadcasting sexually explicit material in violation of 
federal indecency rules the federal communications commission said 
friday 
the action against wfbqfm owned by great american television 
and radio co in cincinnati was the latest in a spate of moves in 
the past year by a newly constituted fcc bent on cracking down on 
disc jockeys often called shock jocks 
