the soviet union is tightening its border controls 
because of smuggling and profiteering that has stripped store 
shelves in the western part of the country premier nikolai i 
ryzhkov announced friday 
also friday mikhail s gorbachevs top advisers huddled in the 
kremlin to outline longdelayed reforms for salvaging the soviet 
economy gorbachev said his concept for a union of sovereign 
republics and the transfer to a market economy are linked 
in a nationally televised address ryzhkov said the border 
restrictions which were relaxed in september 1988 are being 
tightened temporarily because of the abnormal situation on the 
western soviet border he did not elaborate on what the tighter 
restrictions would entail 
ryzhkov said soviets and residents of unspecified neighboring 
countries were taking advantage of the considerably cheaperpriced 
soviet consumer goods and engaging in smuggling and rampant 
blackmarketeering 
he said the situation has the potential to become uncontrollable 
ryzhkov said he signed a decision thursday to repeal the 
simplified rules for crossing the soviet border until such time as 
border and customs services can ensure normal relations with 
neighboring nations 
the simplified rules loosened restrictions on residents of 
border areas to cross the frontier and export goods recently 
however customs officials have been rigorously searching vehicles 
to look for goods being taken out of the soviet union 
on thursday the polish government said it was seeking the 
lifting of travel restrictions imposed on foreign visitors to the 
western ukrainian city of lvov where authorities have barred 
tourists cars and said scarce goods will be confiscated if 
foreigners try to take them away 
