the median price of single family homes in the 
washington dc metropolitan area dropped 5 percent between april 
1989 and april 1990 the first decline in the past decade 
the median sale price of homes in the area dropped from 202239 
a year ago to 191985 according to real estate transaction 
records compiled by silver spring mdbased rufus k lusk amp son 
rufus k lusk sr president of the company said the decline 
was indicative of a readjustment in a real estate market that has 
become both unbalanced an overly expensive 
he said home prices in the washington area have risen so quickly 
in recent years they simply have outstripped peoples incomes in 
many cases he said 
the median price the midpoint figure at which half the homes 
sold for more and half sold for less was considered statistically 
more significant than the average price lusk said 
he said the average could easily skewered by a relatively few 
transactions such as the sales of large estates 
