nasa workers tightened most of the 
48 bolts on one of space shuttle atlantis fuel lines friday but 
the space agency wont know whether that fixed a hydrogen leak 
until a tanking test next week 
the shuttles classified defense department mission is on hold 
until the problem is resolved 
all the bolts checked out fine said nasa spokeswoman lisa 
malone everything looked normal she said 
discovery meanwhile has joined the other two shuttles with 
problems 
one of 14 thrusters on discoverys right orbital maneuvering 
system pad was dented when it fell off a work stand thursday a new 
600000 thruster which weighs 20 pounds and is about the size of 
a football will be installed 
the accident occurred during routine maintenance work malone 
said 
