a black man walking with his white girlfriend 
was chased by a white man into the path of a truck that hit him 
leaving him critically injured in what police said was a racially 
motivated attack 
daniel porter 21 of baltimore was charged with assault and 
reckless endangerment for chasing herbert jennings 38 also of 
baltimore on thursday night porter was being held friday pending 
a bail hearing 
jennings and his 32yearold white girlfriend whom police would 
not identify were taunted shortly before 10 pm thursday by two 
white men in a pickup truck as they walked on a street in the 
highlandtown neighborhood of southeast baltimore not far from 
where the girlfriend lives police said 
