in its june 1989 lawsuit 
rocky flats 16 miles northwest of denver makes plutonium 
triggers for nuclear weapons plutonium processing there has been 
suspended until the plants safety procedures are upgraded 
david simonson doe deputy director of rocky flats said in a 
telephone interview friday that the agency agreed to drop its 
contention that it did not need a permit before using the 
incinerators 
the incinerators never have been used to dispose of wastes mixed 
with plutonium at the plant and simonson said there are no plans 
to use them for that purpose 
the sierra club and doe have been at odds since 1987 when the 
