<TEXT>
while movie theaters on the main 
drag play the loud and violent films of summer a quiet gentle 
show called pageant of the masters is doing turnaway business 
a few blocks away 
this annual stage spectacle coupled with a colorful art 
festival is such a boxoffice hit that it needs no help from the 
national endowment for the arts instead it will be giving money 
back to the community which plays host to this cultural jewel 
as far as i know this is the only town that is paid by the 
arts said jacquie moffett president of the festival of the 
arts who noted that the city of laguna beach receives about 
300000 a year from the sevenweek art extravaganza which runs 
from july through aug 26 
were a nonprofit organization and we do make money she 
said explaining why much of the income from admission tickets is 
given away both to the city and in scholarships to talented 
residents 
the pageant of the masters centerpiece of the laguna beach art 
festival is an outdoor twohour production in which great 
paintings sculpture and even pieces of jewelry are reproduced 
larger than life size on a carefully lit stage 
if the people in these art works appear lifelike its because 
they are real people the concept of living pictures once an 
entertainment of the french court first came to laguna beach 58 
years ago residents their faces and bodies painted and costumed 
pose in exact duplicates of famous works of art 
in an outdoor bowl under the stars these frozen images are 
accompanied by lyrical music and narration which tells the history 
of the art work on view 
with advanced makeup and lighting techniques its often hard to 
tell that living breathing individuals are wearing the paint and 
costumes of the scene standing without visibly blinking or 
breathing 
they are taught a shallow method of breathing and you really 
cant see them breathe said sally reeve longtime public 
relations director for the festival who used to appear in the 
pageant herself 
staying still is stressed above everything said moffett 
noting that this years show features several small children who 
managed to not move a muscle 
sometimes the performers ability to stand still is severely 
tested 
once a pigeon came and landed on a nude moffett recalls 
she just stood there like she was a statue 
because the show is held outdoors she said theres the added 
problem of insects which sometimes land and get stuck in a 
performers makeup 
thats particularly difficult if its one of the nudes she 
said 
the pageant is an allyear project for laguna beach residents 
who not only perform but help select the works to be depicted a 
staff of detectives searches out the owners of paintings or 
sculptures to obtain permission for its use in the pageant of the 
masters 
