washington ap when jesse jackson describes his career plans 
he says he is running for us senator from the district of 
columbia theres no such office but he thinks there should be 
jackson actually is running for shadow senator an unpaid 
lobbyist post for dc statehood the crusade has been a magnet for 
scorn and skepticism 
hes been labeled his shadowship by one acerbic commentator 
and deemed increasingly irrelevant by another futile playacting 
some say a phony job when he could have had a real one outdated 
protest politics outside the mainstream the kiss of death for a 
third presidential bid 
