<TEXT>
the explosion of a bomb in the building housing 
londons stock exchange did not disrupt stock trading today because 
share dealing takes place away from the exchange floor 
there were no injuries in the blast although it caused 
extensive damage 
share prices actually rose during the incident by about 1215 
pm 715 am edt the financial timesstock exchange 100share 
index was up 11 points or 05 percent at 23983 
options trading was disrupted however 
the exchange buildings largely deserted groundlevel trading 
floor houses the london traded options market options are the 
right to buy or sell shares at a fixed price before a specific date 
since britains huge big bang deregulation nearly four years 
ago british and foreign shares have been traded by telephones and 
computers away from the stock exchanges modern tower in the heart 
of the city of london the financial district 
the explosion in a restroom near the exchanges floor viewing 
gallery came at 849 am 349 am edt 40 minutes after a 
telephone warning of an irish republican army bomb police said 
the building on broad street was evacuated before the bomb exploded 
under the british stock trading system market makers at 
scattered designated investment firms track markets in different 
stocks 
the exchange requires them to quote prices continuously through 
the official trading day which runs from 830 am to 430 pm 
trading also is allowed to take place outside official hours 
the market makers prices appear on the exchanges computerized 
price quotations system seaq international 
the london market is europes biggest and forms part of the 
socalled golden triangle with tokyo and new york on the new 
york and tokyo stock exchange specialists in stocks conduct buying 
and selling on the floor 
the london exchange has been studying what it should do with its 
deserted floor the options market plans to move out 
visitors still flock to the exchanges viewing gallery over the 
