<TEXT>
although a bomb extensively damaged londons stock 
exchange friday it would take a largescale computer failure to 
interfere with stock trading in london 
because stock trading no longer takes place on the exchanges 
floor but is now done via telephones and computers the morning 
explosion in a restroom near the exchangefloor viewing gallery 
didnt disrupt business at the stock exchanges modern tower in the 
heart of the city of london 
if the purpose of this callous act was to bring the city 
financial district to a halt they have failed singularly said 
andrew hugh smith chairman of the stock exchange our systems 
and services have functioned perfectly and trading has continued 
as normal 
like other recent bombing incidents in britain this blast was 
linked to the irish republican armys campaign against british rule 
in northern ireland 
earlier attacks have been largely directed at police army and 
government targets the ira however espouses a socialist future 
for a united ireland and stock exchanges are considered an obvious 
target for foes of capitalism 
exchanges employ entrance guards bouncers and metal detactors 
to protect themselves from attack 
despite the explosion prices rose the financial timesstock 
exchange 100share index was up 128 points or 05 percent at 
24001 at the close trading was active 
options trading was disrupted for the day however although the 
exchange building is now largely deserted the groundlevel trading 
floor still houses the london traded options market options are 
the right to buy or sell shares at a fixed price before a specific 
date 
since britains huge deregulation nearly four years ago known 
as the big bang traders no longer physically congregate in one 
place rather designated investment firms make markets in 
different stocks and bonds via an electronic market run with 
computers 
the exchange requires the 25 equities market makers to quote 
prices continuously through the official trading day which runs 
from 830 am to 430 pm london time trading also is allowed to 
take place outside official hours 
the market makers prices appear on the exchanges computerized 
price quotations system seaq international which buyers and 
sellers can view on video display terminals 
on the new york and tokyo stock exchanges trading physically 
takes place on the floor conducted by market makers known as 
specialists 
the london market is europes biggest and forms part of the 
socalled golden triangle with new york and tokyo 
there are more than 2500 british and overseas companies listed 
on londons stock exchange average daily trading in domestic 
stocks is worth about 15 billion 
formally called the international stock exchange of the united 
kingdom and the republic of ireland ltd it employs nearly 2600 
people who develop trading rules list companies record 
transactions and operate information systems 
the tower one of 14 buildings the exchange occupies opened in 
1973 located in broad street it is next to the bank of england 
and across from the grand columned royal exchange which houses 
the london international financial futures exchange 
the london exchange has been studying what it should do with all 
its empty floor space the options market plans to move out 
