soybean futures prices fell sharply friday on the 
chicago board of trade amid forecasts for a weekend of beneficial 
rain in the midwest where crop weather has been nearly perfect for 
most of the summer 
corn and wheat futures closed lower oats were narrowly mixed 
on other commodity markets petroleum futures were mixed 
livestock and meat futures were mixed copper futures rose and 
precious metals slipped 
