at 1 pm edt on the board of trade 
crop prices have been falling since late june largely due to a 
pattern of mild temperatures and frequent precipitation in the 
nations midsection that has facilitated corn and soybean 
development 
this week showers began watering midwestern croplands wednesday 
night continued into friday and were expected to spread during the 
weekend into the mississippi delta region a soybean production 
area that has been fairly dry 
