governments rose 132 point to point intermediate maturities 
rose 516 point and longterm issues added as much as 316 point 
according to telerate inc a financial information service 
the movement of a point is equivalent to a change of 10 in the 
price of a bond with a 1000 face value 
the shearson lehman hutton daily treasury bond index which 
measures price movements on all outstanding treasury issues with 
maturities of a year or longer gained 143 to 116061 
yields on threemonth treasury bills fell to 777 percent as the 
discount dropped 1 basis point to 753 percent yields on sixmonth 
bills rose to 784 percent as the discount gained 1 basis point to 
745 percent yields on oneyear bills were unchanged at 784 
percent as the discount held at 733 percent 
a basis point is onehundredth of a percentage point the yield 
is the annualized return on an investment in a treasury bill the 
discount is the percentage that bills are selling below the face 
value which is paid at maturity 
the federal funds rate the interest rate banks charge each 
other on overnight loans was quoted at 8 percent unchanged from 
late thursday 
