results 
kellogg reported net income of 1357 million or 113 a share 
in the three months ending june 30 up from 1297 million or 
106 a share in the second quarter of 1989 
net sales edged up to 126 billion from 123 billion in the 
1989 period the company said 
the performance of our us readytoeat cereal business was 
down during the quarter said william e lamothe chairman and 
chief executive officer growth of the category has slowed and 
competition remains intense 
competitors with popular oatbran products narrowed kelloggs 
us cereal market lead in 1989 lamothe said the company expects 
new products to widen the lead again 
kellogg introduced two healthoriented oriented cereals 
heartwise and oatbake last fall launched kenmei rice bran in 
january and introduced bigg mixx multigrain cereal marketed 
mainly to children in may 
for the first six months of the year kellogg said it had net 
earnings of 232 million or 192 a share on net sales of 247 
billion compared with 2892 million or 236 a share on net 
sales of 237 billion in the first half of 1989 
