<TEXT>
mcdonalds corp reported friday a 10 
percent increase in secondquarter net income due in part to an 
increase in the number of overseas restaurants 
net income was 2158 million up from 196 million for the same 
quarter last year earnings per share rose 11 percent to 59 cents 
from 53 cents 
company officials also reported an increase in revenues in the 
second quarter from 15 billion in the 1989 period to 17 
billion this year 
mcdonalds said this was the 101st consecutive quarter that the 
company has reported record increases in operating results 
our growth strategy continues to focus on adding restaurants 
building sales at existing restaurants and improving international 
profitability said mcdonalds chairman and chief executive 
officer michael r quinlan 
quinlan said sales in restaurants inside the united states did 
not increase as much as expected 
although us sales are softer than expected we continue to 
see strong growth outside of the us he said 
for the first six months of the year mcdonalds reported net 
income of 3739 million or 102 per share up from 3377 or 90 
cents a share in the first six months of 1989 revenues were 32 
billion up from 29 billion in the previous year 
