<TEXT>
six classaction lawsuits have been 
filed against united telecommunications inc accusing the company 
of failing to keep market analysts and investors informed of 
financial problems at the parent of us sprint a company spokesman 
said friday 
on tuesday united telecom reported its earnings fell 55 percent 
in the second quarter due largely to problems at sprint the 
longdistance phone company of which it is majority owner the 
earnings report sent united telecoms share price tumbling 
five of the suits were filed in us district court in kansas 
city kan while the sixth was filed in federal court in kansas 
city mo said syd courson a sprint spokesman united telecom had 
no comment on the suits he said 
